children.value:
Interface for dynamically generated style images. This is a specification for
implementers to model: it is not an exported method or class.

Images implementing this interface can be redrawn for every frame. They can be used to animate
icons and patterns or make them respond to user input. Style images can implement a
StyleImageInterface#render

method. The method is called every frame and
can be used to update the image.

tags.title: example

children.value: Add an animated icon to the map.
Optional method called when the icon is removed from the map with
Map#removeImage

.
This gives the image a chance to clean up resources and event listeners.

tags.description: The Map this custom layer was just added to.
tags.name: map

children.value: The Map this custom layer was just added to.

This method is called once before every frame where the icon will be used.
The method can optionally update the image's
data
member with a new image.
If the method updates the image it must return
true

to commit the change.
If the method returns
false
or nothing the image is assumed to not have changed.
If updates are infrequent it maybe easier to use
Map#updateImage

to update
the image instead of implementing this method.

tags.title: return
tags.description: `true` if this method updated the image. `false` if the image was not changed.

children.value: true
if this method updated the image.
false
if the image was not changed.
